<section style="background: var(--cream-2);">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="two-col reverse">
      <div>
        <span class="eyebrow">Our Location</span>
        <h2>{{ site.acres }} acres of Central Texas.</h2>
        <p>We're 68 miles south of Austin and 42 miles east of San Antonio. The sanctuary sits in the middle of beautiful sprawling Texas acreage dotted with majestic live oaks, mesquite trees, hackberries, prickly pear cactus, and blanketed in spring with wildflowers.</p>
        <p>This former cattle ranch teems with native fauna. Our cattle, horses, and donkeys share large wooded pastures with whitetail deer, bobcats, badgers, jackrabbits, cottontails, coyotes, feral pigs, diverse reptiles and amphibians, and incredible birds: crested caracaras (also known as Mexican Eagles), red-tailed hawks, several owl species, and two types of vultures.</p>
        <p>Migrating songbirds stop here. Water birds like black-bellied whistling ducks, egrets, Egyptian geese, and great blue herons frequent our ponds. In summer, cattle egrets follow the cows around patiently waiting for insects. And starting in October, like clockwork, about 1,000 great-tailed grackles make SARA their fall and winter home.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="img" style="background: url('/images/ducks.webp') center/cover;"></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

